# MNUDA Styling Guidelines

## Primary Color Palette



### Tailwind Classes
- `text-mnuda-light-blue` - Light blue text
- `bg-mnuda-light-blue` - Light blue background
- `border-mnuda-light-blue` - Light blue border
- `text-mnuda-dark-blue` - Dark navy text
- `bg-mnuda-dark-blue` - Dark navy background
- `border-mnuda-dark-blue` - Dark navy border

## Design Principles

### Typography
- Use clean, modern sans-serif fonts
- Maintain good contrast with dark navy (#014463) on light backgrounds
- Use light blue (#1dd1f5) sparingly for emphasis and CTAs

### Components
- Buttons: Use dark navy background with white text for primary actions
- Secondary buttons: Use light blue background with dark navy text
- Cards/Modals: White background with subtle shadows
- Borders: Use light blue for active states, dark navy for subtle borders

### Spacing & Layout
- Use consistent padding and margins
- Maintain proper visual hierarchy
- Ensure responsive design across all screen sizes

### Interactive Elements
- Hover states: Slightly darker shade of the base color
- Focus states: Light blue outline for accessibility
- Disabled states: Muted colors with reduced opacity

## Component Guidelines

### Buttons
```tsx
// Primary Button
<button className="bg-mnuda-dark-blue text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-opacity-90 transition-colors">
  Primary Action
</button>

// Secondary Button  
<button className="bg-mnuda-light-blue text-mnuda-dark-blue px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-opacity-90 transition-colors">
  Secondary Action
</button>
```

### Cards/Modals
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
  Content here
</div>
```

### Text Hierarchy
```tsx
<h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-mnuda-dark-blue">Main Heading</h1>
<h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-mnuda-dark-blue">Sub Heading</h2>
<p className="text-gray-700">Body text</p>
<span className="text-mnuda-light-blue">Highlighted text</span>
```

## Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient color contrast ratios
- Use focus indicators for keyboard navigation
- Provide alternative text for icons and images
- Test with screen readers

## Brand Consistency
- Always use the defined color palette
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Follow the established component patterns
- Keep the design clean and professional
